The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New York, May 13 (PTI): An Indian mother of three was mowed down by a van outside her East Meadow home on Thursday night. Nina Sharma, 49, was hurled at least 30 feet down the street. Her husband, Rajinder, ran out after hearing a thump.

 Nina, who suffered massive and fatal head trauma, was pronounced dead at the Nassau University Medical Centre.

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has directed the city government to take action against private schools that pay less to teachers than prescribed under the Delhi School Education Act. The director of education and the additional director have been asked to file an action taken report within six weeks weeks by a division bench of Chief Justice M.K. Sharma and Justice Sanjeev Khanna.

 New Delhi (PTI): Himachal Futuristic Communications has distanced itself from ex-director Vinay Maloo after income-tax raids on the firm last week. We would like to clarify that Vinay Maloo had resigned from the board of HFCL and its subsidiary company HFCL Infotel Ltd on October 31, 2006, its managing director said.

 Balaghat (PTI): The chairperson of the local municipality and two officials were booked for allegedly abusing a deputy collector and his team. Police said the team was collecting records of purchases following a complaint about irregularities. 

 Jaipur (PTI): A toddler who was one of the 35 people injured in a LPG cylinder blast in Jodhpur on Friday has succumbed to injuries, police said. Sarpraj, 8, died at the MGH Hospital.

 Chennai (PTI): A garment firm claimed to have woven the worlds longest sari in a non-stop 18-day effort. The 685-metre sari was recently made for the presiding deity of Parshwa Padmavathi Jain temple at Krishnagiri, said the managing partner of Kumaran Silks.




